The paper deals with information theory and channel coding, which are typically categorized under cs.IT. The paper also discusses the ordering of information sets of polar codes, which falls under the category of coding theory, and can be categorized under cs.SI. The paper also discusses the cut criterion and channel symmetrization, which are tools used in optimization and graph theory, respectively, and can be categorized under cs.CC and cs.DS. Finally, the paper discusses potential applications of the results to machine learning, which can be categorized under cs.LG.
